The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Essar acquires ChrysCap BPO 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Feb. 20: After announcing a string of investments in the chemical industry, the Ruias are looking to strengthen their exposure to the business process outsourcing (BPO) segment. 

 The Essar group today announced that its principal holding company, Essar Global, has acquired Global Vantedge, a BPO company owned by ChrysCapital, for an undisclosed sum. 

 Global Vantedge has over 1,400 employees with facilities in Gurgaon and San Jose, Costa Rica. It operates in the banking, telecom and automobile verticals and has some leading companies in its portfolio. 

 The acquisition is expected to contribute over $25 million in revenue to Essars BPO business. This is Essars fourth acquisition in the last one year. The previous three were Customer First and Orion in India and Technion in the US. 

 The Essar group now has a presence in the BPO segment through its wholly owned subsidiary Aegis BPO. 

 Aegis operates integrated back-office and value added services. The company currently has revenues in excess of $180 million and it is Indias fifth largest BPO company. Aegis has centres across the US and India with over 9,000 employees with expertise in telecom, insurance, banking and healthcare. 




